<li class="review">
<article id="review-6588">
<header>
<img src="//i.imgur.com/02pWSq0.jpg" class="review-author-avatar">
<h4 class="review-title">Impressive: Reads like a proper Novel<span class="upvotes"></span><span class="downvotes"></span></h4>
<a href="#review-6588"><time>11/01/15</time></a>
<span class="review-author">By Ardent</span>
</header>
<div class="review-body-wrapper">
<div class="review-body">
<div class="rates">
<span>Overall Score</span>
<span class="review-overall-score score" score="10"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
<span>Style Score</span>
<span class="review-overall-score score" score="10"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
<span>Story Score</span>
<span class="review-overall-score score" score="10"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
<span>Grammar Score</span>
<span class="review-overall-score score" score="10"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
<span>Character Score</span>
<span class="review-overall-score score" score="10"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
</div>
<div class="review-content"><p>Thus is a Solid work of fiction full of details and it reads like a proper novel and not something haphazardly put together. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>The extent of detail indicates that the author puts a lot of thought into the written work. One gets the impression that there is a plan in the way the information is laid out giving the feeling of reading something truely unique. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>The style differes from other FFs in that it’s like a script for a play with some naration mixed in and it makes very easy to read, and at times it’s very enjoyable. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>The setting of an Alternate reality Simulation is incredibly complex but the Author has done a very good job in world creation: very Impressive! .</p>
<p> </p>
<p>As Expected some like @shyntar &amp; @rejin don’t seem to understand the concept of an Alternate Reality Simulation and confuse it with a VRMMRPG; It can’t be helped! </p>
<p> </p>
<p>As for Character development the Author seems to be painfully trying to build a realistic personality in order to avoid an OP MC. I must say that in a forum where most prefer an OP the Author is very brave.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>As someone who appreciates something more than Simplistic I apreciate the Author’s attempt to produce a truly original written work of fanatic built around an original concept and look forward to more from the Author. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>All in all Impressive FF</p>
<p>Thanks. </p>
</div>
 
</div>
</div>
