							<img src="//i.imgur.com/02pWSq0.jpg" class="review-author-avatar">
							<h4 class="review-title">Not your usual VRRMMO<span class="upvotes"></span><span class="downvotes"></span></h4>
							<a href="#review-14159"><time>20/03/15</time></a>
							<span class="review-author">By koutacchi</span>
						</header>
						<div class="review-body-wrapper">
							<div class="review-body">
								<div class="rates">
																											<span>Overall Score</span>
									<span class="review-overall-score score" score="9"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
																			<span>Style Score</span>
										<span class="review-overall-score score" score="9"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
										<span>Story Score</span>
										<span class="review-overall-score score" score="10"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
										<span>Grammar Score</span>
										<span class="review-overall-score score" score="9"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
										<span>Character Score</span>
										<span class="review-overall-score score" score="7"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
																										</div>
								<div class="review-content"><p>I&#8217;d say, the details of this fiction is great! I&#8217;m even suprised at how you tried to convey the backstory of the game first which is a plus for me.</p>
<p>The way the story was handled is unique in itself.</p>
<p>This time the VRRMMO&#8217;s story is based on a guild scale not your usual MC fighting alone at the start and gains level. As what the author said on the synopsis, he got inspired by a couple of novels and one of which is heavily inspired would be Log Horizon as it seems like the beginning story is filled with details about MC&#8217;s community and how will they build up their group. Truly a new way of showing how VRRMMO works in such scale, much less how you would think a community of dark gamers would plan. I&#8217;m looking forward for more of this story as it is really interesting as the story goes. </p>
<p>Though the only downside for this would be a lack of spotlight for the MC, let&#8217;s just see how things would go.</p>
</div>
								<!--div class="review-content"></div-->
							</div>
						</div>
						<footer class="rate-footer">
							<div class="thumbs" rid="14159">
								<a class="upvote">&#xf164;<span>0</span></a>
