				</li>
								<li class="review">
					<article id="review-18524">
						<header>
							<img src="//i.imgur.com/02pWSq0.jpg" class="review-author-avatar">
							<h4 class="review-title">My Serious Review<span class="upvotes"></span><span class="downvotes"></span></h4>
							<a href="#review-18524"><time>30/04/15</time></a>
							<span class="review-author">By Lich</span>
						</header>
						<div class="review-body-wrapper">
							<div class="review-body">
								<div class="rates">
																											<span>Overall Score</span>
									<span class="review-overall-score score" score="6"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
																										</div>
								<div class="review-content"><p>First thing first I&#8217;d like to tell you that I like the Idea of alternative reality simulation, it&#8217;s like bringing the idea of reincarnation into reality, a second life simulation in an epic world, it&#8217;s so fascinating! Therefore I give you 6 out of ten. What hold me to give you a perfect score was because the story line was narowed only to a Nordic myth, that looks too shallow. Myth doesn&#8217;t belong only to Europe, it&#8217;s all over the earth bro. If you could combine it you&#8217;ll create a super wonderful novel that can compete even harry potter fame and beat my current no.1 favorit LMS.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>I like details but too much details on every things is a bother, my suggestion you could put all those details and wrap it on side story or extra. Something like &#8220;the hobbit&#8221; or harry potter extra, that&#8217;ll be awesome! Talking about details then a consistent strory line is MUST! Like a train, it may make a turn left and right but it still on the rails and not jumping on all over the place. If you could add more linked story to the future and the past, that&#8217;ll be super GREAT! it will give more thrills and curiosity that&#8217;ll make all readers goes crazy.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Last, there is a big problem here. When I follow the story I end up in a conclusion, it&#8217;s a story of a very lucky-a naive and bastard rich kid-a broken hearted dude playing with his money. This kill my mood one time. Inside I found out that it is a world of money and the rich only, everything is about money money and money farming so much that this novel end up like an economic story wraped in a nordic myth. That kill my mood two times. There is no hardship since everyone can just buy everything, no great adventure and achievements but a story of money making money, at this rate I start to wonder if your intention actually writing an aconomic book about how rich kids plays with their money. This kill my mood three times.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>The novel started with a myth stories, and even though you&#8217;ve set it as an alternative reality simulation but there is still so much game characteristics in it. In short it&#8217;s actually an alternative reality simulation game and not a pure virtual alternative reality simulation which is full of &#8220;a real hard work with hands&#8221; stories. There is your big blunder, you don&#8217;t stick with the idea or maybe you just can&#8217;t  recognize the idea. You have killed the adventure, you have killed the imagination of a myth world, you&#8217;ve killed the &#8220;hard work&#8221; development history, you&#8217;ve killed &#8220;the epic&#8221; struggle. Instead you&#8217;ve replaced it only with a story of a businessman money farming in a  game. You&#8217;ve succesfully killed all the joy and excitement of a myth world virtual reality. That killed my mood big time.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>From every angle you were looks like narrowing your readers only to the &#8220;selected very few people&#8221; only, if that was your true intention than I have no comment about it. If was not because the fresh idea of virtual alternate reality simulation, I will pass your novel without a second thought. But since I see so much possibilities on it, I gladly overview it for you with a good intentions of course. It will be a big bother for you to start all over from the scratch, and since it still on early stage there is still so much room for plot twist and a better development. My final suggestion, DON&#8217;T KILL ALL THE JOY!. And over all I support and hope a better work from you.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>With regards.</p>
</div>
								<!--div class="review-content"></div-->
							</div>
						</div>
