				</li>
								<li class="review">
					<article id="review-6526">
						<header>
							<img src="//i.imgur.com/02pWSq0.jpg" class="review-author-avatar">
							<h4 class="review-title">like the idea, but not the execution<span class="upvotes"></span><span class="downvotes"></span></h4>
							<a href="#review-6526"><time>11/01/15</time></a>
							<span class="review-author">By rejin</span>
						</header>
						<div class="review-body-wrapper">
							<div class="review-body">
								<div class="rates">
																											<span>Overall Score</span>
									<span class="review-overall-score score" score="7"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
																										</div>
								<div class="review-content"><p>Let me start by saying that i skipped the prologue simply because i don&#8217;t like reading background story of the world, this is by no means the fault of this fiction.</p>
<p>I would also like to say that this review comes over way more negative than i actually view the fiction.</p>
<p>I recommend any person to read to at least the end of Chapter 3: Benefits of Open Beta before judging this series since no review can tell you whether you&#8217;ll like this story or not.</p>
<p>The first thing i encountered in this fiction was a whole lot of information, so much that i just skimmed through it. which is fine since it&#8217;s not a must to know the information but i&#8217;d like to say that since the average viewer, unlike you, is not being busy with this fiction every day they will most likely remember very little of it.</p>
<p>I do however like the names you choose for your companions, since they&#8217;re easy to remember.</p>
<p>the thing that intrigues me the most is how this fiction is clan-based, the MC and his clan need to do tasks while the MC needs to develop his clan to meet a quota without making the clan OP.</p>
<p>The thing I think this fiction should do without is the real life money used inside of the game. it completely throws away the feeling of the main character creating his own clan. it erases the hardships of creating it and erases the bond the reader has to it. not only that it feels to me that any achievement they get amounts to nothing because they used real money to advance past the normal players.</p>
<p>A way I personally think might be better without changing the first chapters too much would be to allow players to form clans before they start the game and give those clans a set amount of points, thus forcing people to balance the amount of people in a clan vs the quality of the members (100 vs 1000, not 10 vs 100)</p>
<p>I still follow this story (I don&#8217;t follow that many, 5-6 out of the many i read on this site) but I just wanted to say this because I would&#8217;ve enjoyed this way more if those things would&#8217;ve been different.</p>
</div>
								<!--div class="review-content"></div-->
							</div>
