				</li>
								<li class="review">
					<article id="review-3904">
						<header>
							<img src="//oi57.tinypic.com/kbem3m.jpg" class="review-author-avatar">
							<h4 class="review-title">I uh... what?<span class="upvotes"></span><span class="downvotes"></span></h4>
							<a href="#review-3904"><time>13/12/14</time></a>
							<span class="review-author">By Shyntar</span>
						</header>
						<div class="review-body-wrapper">
							<div class="review-body">
								<div class="rates">
																											<span>Overall Score</span>
									<span class="review-overall-score score" score="4"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
																			<span>Style Score</span>
										<span class="review-overall-score score" score="5"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
										<span>Story Score</span>
										<span class="review-overall-score score" score="5"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
										<span>Grammar Score</span>
										<span class="review-overall-score score" score="7"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
										<span>Character Score</span>
										<span class="review-overall-score score" score="4"><p>&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;&#xf005;</p></span>
																										</div>
								<div class="review-content"><p>Edit:To the above comment from the author, it&#8217;s <em>Shyntar </em>(Cute typo ;P) I stand by what I wrote (except for maybe the university thing, we might have a misunderstanding that department).  Typing up a PM to address your individual points right now since sadly, the reply function doesn&#8217;t work here.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>So usually I hate giving out negative reviews and don’t bother, especially this early in the series, but something about this story…</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Three chapters in as of writing this including the prologue, but honestly chapter 2 could just be considered the world setting/game guide. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>The author starts off with a bold proclamation of a set word count for his chapters that simultaneously gives me hope for the story and manages to come off as a backhanded insult to people who write small chapters that sets me on edge.  To be fair he does seem to stick to his self-imposed word count of 5000.  Sadly most of it seems to be repetitive filler such as typing said: “Open &lt;skill/window/whatever&gt;” three times instead of just mentioning they all said it at the same time.  Oh and numbers.  Lots and lots of numbers.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>This is followed by mentioning a disdain of overpowered protagonists and promises that there will none of that in<em> this</em> story!  No sir!  Another beacon of hope!  Then the MC turns out to have started college at the ripe age of 14 and has four of five doctorates.  But he’s not a genius, nope.  Because true genius is a myth and if you disagree, apparently you are an idiot.  And within the game?  There’s a certain amount of randomness in character creation and the MC just happened to get a sub-race that has a .01% chance to proc.  But don’t worry, it’s terribly bad. ‘The cursed race’!  So cursed in fact, that it’s overflowing  divine power  makes it glow in such a manner that you need an <em>advanced magic skill</em> to shut. It. Off.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>The actual story as far as I can tell is ‘Gold Farming Incorporated’.  The game itself seems terrible and unfun, though the author himself points out that it is not in fact a game but a ‘Reality Simulation’.  Except you need to spend 20 real dollars in said game to learn to shoot a bow.  And that’s one of the cheapest.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Grammar isn’t too bad.  There’s some misspelled words here and there, the structure seems to switch between an instruction manual and some sort of movie-like script but it’s readable. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Strangely, despite all this, there’s something there, some spark of interesting.   I’m holding out hope and will keep an eye on it.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Oh and I don’t know if this is intentional, but women, both specifically mentioned and in general have been mentioned about three times.  And they are apparently all shallow, untrustworthy creatures that are easily swayed by pretty, sparkly things (like say… our perma-glowing MC).</p>
</div>
								<!--div class="review-content"></div-->
							</div>
						</div>
